President Obama met with Chinese President Xi Jinping in Peru and discussed the progress made in strengthening the bilateral relationship between the US and China. They highlighted joint accomplishments in various areas, including climate change. They also addressed the threat posed by North Korea's nuclear weapons and affirmed their commitment to denuclearization. President Obama encouraged China to advance reforms in its economic model and address excess capacity in industrial sectors. Both leaders emphasized the importance of a stable and productive relationship between the US and China.